12/17/80	get_mode

Syntax:  get_mode MODE_STR MODE_NAME


Function:	 extracts the value of a mode from a mode string.


Arguments:
MODE_STR
   is a mode string, as used with an I/O module.
MODE_NAME
   is the name of a mode contained in the mode string.


Notes:  For a boolean mode, the value returned is "true" or "false",
otherwise it is the character string value of the mode.


Syntax as active function:  [get_mode MODE_STR MODE_NAME]
